On the Democratic side, Bernie Sanders is hands down the most honest man of integrity this country has had run for President in a long time. The question for voters is his economic policies. He wants to spread the wealth under socialism, trying to make that wealthy one percent pay for his programs. Do you believe that can work? I don't think he can make it work, because the wealthy will find ways to keep their money away from the government.<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/newsboy/files/2015/12/bernie-sanders.jpg"><img src="http://www.chicagonow.com/newsboy/files/2015/12/bernie-sanders-300x300.jpg" alt="bernie sanders" width="300" height="300" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-1473" /></a> Then there is Martin O’Malley. He is barely a blip on the polls, but if you have listened to him debate, you know he is smart, had good success as Mayor of Baltimore and then Governor of Maryland and would be a good bet for President. 

