If you look at how movies, television shows, magazines, news shows, talk shows and too many books present that scenario, often times the wrong choice is played up as the fun and exciting choice. "Oh, he’ll never find out," she says. "Oh she’ll never know," he says. Perhaps in many cases that is true, but the cheater will know. Of course that's the choice if there is no acceptance of right or wrong, no moral compass, no voice inside their head and heart saying, “You just made a big mistake! Don’t do it again.”

