Justification usually plays a part in it. "She's so beautiful, I can't help myself!" says the cheating husband. "He's so handsome, I can't say no," says the cheating wife. When you start justifying actions you clearly know are wrong, that should be the first clue. Of course, easier said than done and for many, it feels like an addiction they can't avoid. As an old boss once told me, "People can justify anything, and do."

