Well, that genius pulled his wonderful wife out of the Midwest hometown she loved, put her in a small New York high-rise apartment, alone, while he spent most of the day at a major PR firm where he met and had an affair with a lady 30 years younger than him. When he got the young lady pregnant, his wife divorced him and he moved to London, where his ex-wife and three kids want nothing to do with him any longer. The choices he made, have him living a very lonely, guilt-filled life. He had it all, and now at 70, he will spend his final days alone. That's the risk he took and tried to justify to himself 20 years ago.

I’m Catholic and for me, the choices my old boss made are unimaginable. I'll never understand it or the justifications placed behind it. Like many Christians – certainly not all - I have that moral compass embedded in my heart. Everyone has the thoughts, but it’s about turning away from the actions. Men are experts at not sharing their problems. So most go it alone, trying to figure it out on their own. Of course, the suicide rate for men over 45 is very high and this is one of the reasons.

